    "description": "The Soummam Conference structured and unified the revolution",
    "text": "\n### **Introduction**  \nThe **Soummam Conference**, held on **August 20, 1956**, in **Ifri, Soummam (present-day Béjaïa Province)**, was one of the most significant events in the history of the **Algerian Revolution**. It came at a critical moment when the revolution needed **better organization and unified leadership** to ensure the continuity of the armed struggle against French colonial rule.  \n\n### **Reasons for Holding the Conference**  \nAs the war intensified and the number of freedom fighters increased, the revolution faced major challenges, including **a lack of coordination, multiple leadership factions, and the absence of a unified structure**. Therefore, it became essential to hold a meeting to establish clear guidelines for organizing and managing the revolution.  \n\n### **Key Decisions of the Soummam Conference**  \nThe conference resulted in several fundamental decisions that **strengthened the unity of the revolution**, including:  \n- **Priority of internal leadership over external leadership**, meaning that decisions should be made inside Algeria rather than by leaders abroad.  \n- **Priority of political action over military action**, ensuring that military operations served the revolution’s political objectives.  \n- **Division of Algeria into six military regions**, allowing for better task distribution and more effective coordination.  \n- **Creation of the National Council of the Algerian Revolution (CNRA)** as the highest legislative body and the Coordination and Execution Committee (CCE) as the executive authority.  \n\n### **Impact and Importance of the Conference**  \nThe Soummam Conference helped **unify the revolutionary ranks**, making the movement more **organized and efficient**, which strengthened its resilience against colonial forces. It also gave a significant boost to the revolution’s political path and helped expand Algeria’s diplomatic influence on the international stage.  \n\n### **Conclusion**  \nThe **Soummam Conference** remains a pivotal moment in the history of the **Algerian Revolution**, as it laid the foundation for national struggle and contributed to achieving independence in **1962**. It proved that **organization and strategic planning are just as crucial as armed resistance** in the fight for liberation.  "
